definition:
ἀγαπητός, -ή, -όν 
 (ἀγαπάω), [in LXX chiefly for יָתִיד, יָדִיד ;] 
beloved (see M, Pr., 221); 
  (a) by God: of Christ, Mat.3:17; of men, Rom.1:7; 
   (b) by Christians, of one another: 1Co.4:14; frequently as form of address, ib. 10:14; opposite to ἐχθρός, Rom.11:28 (see AR, Eph., 229; Cremer, 17; MM, VGT, see word).
 (AS)
